post_text:
CJUSD Families

Breakfast and Lunch Meal Combos will be available from 11:00 am – 1:00 pm drive-up style at all of our school sites (excluding McClellan) on scheduled school days.

Parents/Guardians may pick up meals for more than one student as long as each student barcode or student ID number is provided.

Meals will also be delivered at multiple bus stops! For stop locations and times click on the flyer at www.centerusd.org; go to "Site Menu" then click "Nutrition Services Department".

We cannot accept payments at our school sites; payments for meals must be made online at family.titank12.com or in our Nutrition Services Dept.
If you think your student qualifies for Free/Reduced priced meals you may apply online at family.titank12.com or pick up a paper application in our Nutrition Services Dept.

Each enrolled Center Joint Unified Student may pick up one meal combo per meal service day.

Please contact 916-338-6416 with any questions.

CJUSD Nutrition Services

North Country Elementary School
May 28 at 2:08 PM ·

Happy last day of school!

This is with out a doubt the strangest end to a school year I have ever experienced. I miss the smiles and excitement from students and staff as we looked back on memories from the year and look forward to summer fun. Sitting in an empty parking lot feeling a bit lost today. The unknown is scary but I know our North Country Family will pull together and make the best out of whatever comes our way.

I didn't get to play our end of year song so here you go! https://youtu.be/CXFsWAkLoXQ

Have a great summer and please stay safe. Can't hardly wait to see you next year!

Mr. Farrel

North Country Elementary School
May 27 at 12:08 PM ·

Last Week of School
Dear North Country Families,
We are in our final days of the school year and tomorrow is the official last day of school!  The office will be open on Thursday, 5/28, from 8:00-12:00pm for bag pick up, yearbook refunds, and enrollment. Bags not picked up by 12:00pm will be discarded.
Thank you for your flexibility and support in this very unique school year. Once the district has finalized reopening plans for next year we will communicate that information with our families. Wishing you all the very best. Please stay healthy and happy. Looking forward to seeing everyone in the fall.
Warm Regards,
Mr. Farrel

shared_text:
Center High Activities
May 2 at 9:53 AM ·

Top Ten Senior Madison Lacy. Madison will be attending Johns Hopkins University in the Fall. Madison states,”One of my favorite memories at CHS was when my sophomore math teacher, Mr. Palmer, brought ghost pepper sauce for those in the class who wanted to try. The people who were daring enough to taste a drop of the sauce went completely crazy! Everyone was running around, some were tearing up, and one of my friends even got it in her nose. Another one of my friends tried washing out the burn with his classic three bread sandwich. To sum it up, the mayhem that filled 2nd period math not only made the rest of the day fun, but also was one of my most memorable high school moments.” Congratulations, best wishes and good luck Madison 🎓

Good Afternoon,

As a valued member of our staff and community, you understand the commitment Center Joint Unified School District has to the following:
· Providing instruction that will support all students to move successfully through the
grades and graduate prepared for post-secondary college and career
· Creating a safe, positive learning environment for all students
· Increasing student, parental and family involvement

As we begin to develop our new three-year Local Control and Accountability Plan (LCAP), we desire to broaden our stakeholder input around these district commitments. We are asking that you take a few moments to complete the survey referenced below.

Thank you!

Center Joint Unified School District

Good Afternoon,

As a valued member of our staff and community, you understand the commitment Center Joint Unified School District has to the following:
· Providing instruction that will support all students to move successfully through the
grades and graduate prepared for post-secondary college and career
· Creating a safe, positive learning environment for all students
· Increasing student, parental and family involvement

As we begin to develop our new three-year Local Control and Accountability Plan (LCAP), we desire to broaden our stakeholder input around these district commitments. We are asking that you take a few moments to complete the survey referenced below.

Thank you!

Center Joint Unified School District

LCAP Survey Link: https://forms.gle/1zPd4y16aigAT8t18

DOCS.GOOGLE.COM
2019 Stakeholder Feedback
